# Root .dockerignore — applies when the build context is the monorepo root.
# Mirrored by packages/server/.dockerignore in case a future tool builds from
# the package subdir.

# Dependencies and build output — rebuilt inside the image.
**/node_modules
**/.next
**/dist
**/.turbo
**/*.tsbuildinfo

# Local-only state that has no place in a production image.
**/.git
**/.gitignore
**/.gitattributes
.github/

# CRITICAL: never bake secrets into the image. Keep `.env.example` if you
# want a baseline reference inside the container; we exclude it too for
# tightness — Railway/Docker env vars are the source of truth.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Editor and OS noise.
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/.idea
**/.vscode

# Test artifacts.
**/coverage
**/.nyc_output

# Platform-specific deploy artifacts that are not the Docker path.
**/.vercel

# Logs.
**/*.log
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-debug.log*
**/yarn-error.log*
**/pnpm-debug.log*

# Marketing / dev assets outside the server package.
examples/
**/README.md
**/CHANGELOG.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
LICENSE

# Docker meta — no need to ship it inside the image.
**/Dockerfile
**/.dockerignore
docker-compose*.yml
